Can't find the darn K2 monolith.

Been looking for at least half an hour in the few kilometers where it should be, based on the screenshots in the OP. Any tips?

It's on the "back" side of K2. Back side meaning the West side. It's on quite a slope, but should be visible on most terrain settings. (I think I took this picture on high terrain detail? Maybe not... there were a couple that I still had to drop down to Low to see them.) See that slightly lighter coloured "flat" patch atop K2 near the top of your photo? Look west-southwest from there. It's really, really hard to spot with the stock ground texture.

Edited September 10, 2015 by Cydonian Monk

Yeah that one hassled me for quite some time.

It is on an almost vertical slope and very hard to reach on the west side of the mountainrange.

Dont get fooled by the mapview. It might look like it is on top of the mountain but it is not... more like 1/4 down from the top.

I'm not totally sure if this counts as an easter egg, but the top of the fairing base says "Payload goes here"

I might have discovered an Easter egg on Laythe!

10 hours ago, destra9 said:

I might have discovered an Easter egg on Laythe!

Please share with us , friend ...in spoiler tags, OFC

While Playing around with HyperEdit, I teleported to Laythe and discovered this. The coordinates of the Weird Islands are roughly the same as the KSC Launchpad back on Kerbin. They are perfectly spherical, not visible from the map, not part of Laythe's terrain and you can't land on these islands. Idk what this is if it isn't an Easter Egg.
